article.headline: UC Riverside 70, Cal St.-Fullerton 69
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Kevin Bradshaw's dunk with 3 seconds remaining lifted UC Riverside to a 70-69 win over Cal State-Fullerton on Saturday night. The Highlanders (9-12, 4-5 Big West) got possession for the winning basket with 20 seconds left after a turnover by the Titans (9-15, 5-6). Phil Martin led UC Riverside with 26 points and eight rebounds. He made 4 of 5 3-pointers. Bradshaw finished with 13 points and five rebounds. Perry Webster scored 15 points to lead the Titans, but he committed six turnovers. Devon Peltier added 14 points and Jer'Vaughn Johnson and Orlando Brown scored 11 each. UC Riverside led 37-36 at the half.
